<h2>How to use DentHub</h2>

<p>If you are a patient, and already have an account please <a href="~/Administration/Identity/Login">sign in</a> and schedule your next dentist <a href="~/Appointment/Create">appointment</a> choosing among a multitude of <a href="~/Administration/Clinic/All">clinics</a> and <a href="~/Administration/Dentist">professionals</a>. Once you see your dentist, share your exerience and <a href="~/Rating/Create">rate</a> the appointment.</p>
<p>If you still don't have an account, all you need to do is <a href="~/Administration/Identity/RegisterPatient">register&nbsp;as a patient</a>.</p>
<p>If you are a denitist professional working for one of our clinics, please <a href="~/Administration/Identity/Register">register as a dentist</a> and:</p>
<ul>
    <li>schedule patient <a href="~/Appointment/Create">appointments</a> with one click</li>
    <li>find all your patients' dental records&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
    <li><a href="~/Rating/Create">rate</a> your patient after every appointment&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>Every medical instution can register with DentHub and start using our services. Contact our customer services representatives by emailing <a href="mailto:%20cs@denthub.com">cs@denthub.com</a>.</p>
<p>In search of better services for patients and better patients for our professionals, we will deactivate every clinic, dentist or patient with consistently below expectation ratings.</p>
